			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Theren circled slowly around her opponent, her brow glistening with sweat as the fight had been long and her emotions had been breaking in waves throughout her.  Every time she was in the arena memories of her sister’s death assaulted her and made her reel with strain.  After months of training here, she figured her mentors knew that, which is why they made her fight on these reminiscent soils.  The ability to fight past mental and physical barriers would help her to become the warrior she wanted to be.  Slowly she shook her head to clear her thoughts from going down the path of her sister’s death again, and concentrated on the opponent that stood before her.  When she first started fighting here, every opponent wore a mask of her sister’s face in her mind and made her slow to react, but now she held the sheer force of will to overcome the past and concentrate on the here and now.
<br />

<br />
Today her opponent was Ratraz, the large peacekeeper that everyone saw at the Maiden’s Fancy.  He made his presence known in the tavern with his size and trollish way of handling problems.  What most people who visited did not know, was that there were always three other peacekeepers on duty somewhere in the establishment.  They moved silently through the patrons, or watched from secluded areas, ready to step in if they were needed.  Theren was one of these now, but they always kept her hidden as they felt the patrons that enjoyed her other talents would not want her to give up that aspect and might cause trouble that her job was now to control.  She had changed the way she dressed and bound her hair up, with her build she could not be mistaken for a man, but now when someone, by an off chance, caught a glimpse of her, they noticed the aura of danger about her instead of the air of sexuality.  Twice daily workouts against the other peacekeepers had toned her body to superb shape and her girlish curves had hardened to muscular perfection.  No longer sharing a bed with anyone, but sharing a common sleeping area with the others made her control her sexual appetites, for no pleasure was shared between the peacekeepers and the ladies that worked there, nor among themselves.
<br />

<br />
This was the second of her workouts this day, and this mornings had been versus a former assassin who had vowed to make her remember that sneakiness and cunning could be far more dangerous than the two handed blade Ratraz now used against her.  Her body still stung in places where he had been able to score on her, though never a kill shot.  Pride still streamed through her veins at that, since it was the first time she had ever been able to avoid his well timed and placed blows.  
<br />

<br />
That pride buoyed her spirit in this battle with the troll, but he was not holding back today.  When they first started sparring he would hold back against her and told her that he didn’t want to “crush da girlie.”  Slowly he became more comfortable with her abilities and started challenging her more and more, throwing his weight into her to try and overpower her was now a common tactic.  
<br />

<br />
The tier’dal blinked sweat from her eyes and concentrated on his blade, twice he had tried to bring his hands across and bash the small axe from her main hand.  Fighting with an axe and dagger was an unusual combination but one that Theren was working hard at.  Working with all weapons to hone her skills was necessary, but the axe she used seemed to be the most versatile.  
<br />
Her muscles were starting to tire and her reactions beginning to slow down now and knew if she did not end this soon; her earlier achievement would be stained with a loss to the troll.  She moved quickly to the side, trying a step that the assassin had showed her a week ago, crossing her left foot behind the right she moved back and sideways at the same time looking as though she was distancing herself from him.  
<br />

<br />
That’s when Ratraz made his mistake, he brought his large blade too far out to the right, trying to stop her from moving that direction, but that had not been her intention, she balanced on her left foot then drove a step in with her right.  Closing quickly she brought the axe down at an angle and trapped the troll’s blade between the haft and the head of her smaller axe.  He knew how to counter this maneuver and started to push her back.  Bringing her small dagger in and striking the side of this hilt with hers, over-balanced his movement and forced his grip to loosen, at that moment she pulled back with the axe and sent his blade to the ground, effectively disarming him.
<br />

<br />
Grunting in surprise, he recovered and tried to drop a shoulder forward to take her down and use his strength to grapple with her, but expecting that Theren ducked down under his weight and moved left, tripping him with her shin, then turning and driving the pommel of her dagger into his exposed back.  “Har!” he boomed, “Girlie gut me gud!  Yu be barshing gud, girlie.”  He rolled from under her and clapped her on the shoulder in joy, sending her small frame forward a step and to a knee.  She caught her balance quickly, bringing her axe and dagger to the ready as her downward glace saw a pair of plate boots before her.  Looking up quickly, taking in the armor the he wore, she knew this could be only one man, and trouble for her.  Fayerd ta’Leith, Captain of the church’s guard stood before her, inclining his head in greeting.  
<br />

<br />
He spoke in a voice that echoed in her mind through the panic, calm and sensually deep her body shivered slightly. “Well fought young one.  You show a great deal of promise for one that uses only her talent to fight, not the grace of Innoruk.”  
<br />

<br />
Theren expected a reaction like this from him; she knew how he had moved up the ranks in power from the rumors that passed through the city.  A fighter much like herself with no magic, just a great deal of ability, he was proud in the fact that Innoruk blessed his sword hand and lent him the strength to rise to his current position in the church.  Before this day she sneered when she heard his name, trusting only in her own hand and scorning those, like her parents, that gave a God more reverence than their own abilities, but standing before this man she was struck by the sheer force of his will.
<br />

<br />
She returned his greeting by bowing her own head slightly, “Thank you Revered One.  May I ask what brings you here this day?”  Straightening up before him, and gazing up to meet his eyes challengingly, Theren smiled though her heart was racing in her chest.
<br />

<br />
“You have m’lady.” He paused watching as her eyes sparkled with interest then a touch of fear, “I was sent by the Church to bring you in.  They wish to question you on certain matters.”
<br />

<br />
Ratraz stepped forward picking up his blade, willing to protect his young friend, but she laid a hand gently on his arm smiling up at him.  “Ratraz, we knew this day would come and I could not be left in peace here for long.  Please go tell Belyea that I will be late and where I have gone.”  Theren turned back to Fayerd knowing that the troll would tell her boss and he would do what he could to help her, “I hope you will give me a few moments to prepare myself.” Motioning down to the damp garments clinging to her skin, “I do not wish to soil your temple with my current attire.”
<br />

<br />
He lifted his head slightly, his gaze following her motions.  Desire flashed quickly in his veins, and came under control quickly.  Never had he let his wants or needs interfere with his duty, and he would not let this Sa’Riik child challenge his control.  He knew everything about her since he had people watching her since she left her home.  Every report that came across his desk intrigued him more.  Showing such an ability and will to survive and move up in the world, that he found himself wondering more and more about her.  The prophecy that was given at the birth of her and her sister was still foremost in many minds.  Those that chose to lend strength to the purity of the magic and abilities lent to the by Innoruk, dismissed her as a fighter that had destroyed the chosen one, but he saw beyond that and knew that a fighter such as she held the world in her hand and could do anything she had been prophesized to do, as long as she bathed her self in the glory of Innoruk.  
<br />

<br />
This was the first time Fayerd had seen her in the flesh, but he realized that the reports of the things she had done previously in the tavern were not to be dismissed.  Her strength and sensuality intrigued him as no other woman had done and his dreams of helping her rise to fulfill the prophecy of her birth now expanded on sharing that rise with her, day and night.  He cleared his throat slightly and replied, “Of course not M’lady.  We only want for your comfort in the Glory of our temple.”  He stepped aside to let her move before him.  As she moved past, he reached out and touched the small of her back, moving in beside her.  Her body trembled lightly under his touch as they left the arena and moved towards her quarters behind The Maiden’s Fancy.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=301723" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.thewolfe.net/images/sigs/Saffie_sigs/theren.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
